BT 1 0 0 1 54 549.6 Tm (Ten foundational anomalies in quantum mechanics and particle physics are resolved) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 537.6 Tm (through the coherence decay function C = C_0 exp\(-alpha gamma_eff\). The measurement) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 525.6 Tm (problem, quantum entanglement, Wigner's Friend paradox, quantum Darwinism, CPT) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 513.6 Tm (symmetry, quantum gravity unification, the proton radius puzzle, the neutron) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 501.6 Tm (lifetime discrepancy, the proton spin crisis, and the Boltzmann brain problem each) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 489.6 Tm (yield to a single principle: coherence is a relational, regime-dependent quantity) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 477.6 Tm (that undergoes phase transitions at a critical decoherence rate gamma_c. Measurement) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 465.6 Tm (is not an interpretive choice but a physical phase transition. Entanglement is not) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 453.6 Tm (nonlocal influence but spatially extended coherence. Observer paradoxes dissolve) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 441.6 Tm (because coherence is observer-relative. Quantum mechanics and general relativity) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 429.6 Tm (describe different coherence regimes of the same underlying physics. Each anomaly is) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 417.6 Tm (closed with explicit mechanisms, equations, and testable predictions. This paper) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 405.6 Tm (extends Papers 5 \(REQMT\), 66 \(Bell States\), 84 \(Z2 Symmetry\), and 115 \(Consciousness) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 393.6 Tm (Order Parameter\) in the AIIT-THRESI series.) Tj T* ET
