BT 1 0 0 1 54 351.6 Tm (1. The Coherence Resolution of Quantum Foundations) Tj T* ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 12 TL ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 329.6 Tm (The foundational problems of quantum mechanics are not problems of mathematics. The) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 317.6 Tm (formalism works. They are problems of ontology: what does the formalism describe?) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 305.6 Tm (For nearly a century, the answer has been deferred to interpretation. Copenhagen,) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 293.6 Tm (Many-Worlds, Bohmian mechanics, QBism, relational QM --- each offers a narrative) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 281.6 Tm (overlay on identical predictions.) Tj T* ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 12 TL ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 263.6 Tm (This paper demonstrates that the coherence decay function introduced in Papers 5 and) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 251.6 Tm (84 resolves these problems without interpretive freedom. The function is:) Tj T* ET
BT /F3 8 Tf 9.6 TL ET
BT 1 0 0 1 74 229.6 Tm (C = C_0 * exp\(-alpha * gamma_eff\)) Tj T* ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 12 TL ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 209.6 Tm (where C is the coherence of a quantum system, C_0 is the initial coherence, alpha is) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 197.6 Tm (a coupling constant, and gamma_eff is the effective decoherence rate experienced by) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 185.6 Tm (the system. All foundational paradoxes reduce to misidentifying which coherence) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 173.6 Tm (regime a system occupies or failing to recognize that coherence is relational ---) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 161.6 Tm (different observers at different gamma_eff see different physics.) Tj T* ET
BT /F3 10 Tf 12 TL ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 143.6 Tm (A phase transition occurs at gamma_c. For gamma_eff < gamma_c, the system is) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 131.6 Tm (quantum: superposition, entanglement, and interference dominate. For gamma_eff >) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 119.6 Tm (gamma_c, the system is classical: definite outcomes, locality, and deterministic) Tj T* ET
BT 1 0 0 1 54 107.6 Tm (trajectories emerge. The transition is sharp, physical, and measurable.) Tj T* ET
